    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-09-08T06:54:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-09-08T06:54:00-05:00" n="803"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d803">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">890F.24/9–844: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Appointed Minister to Saudi Arabia</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Eddy</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Extract]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Jidda</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-09-08T15:00:00+03:06"
                            >September 8, 1944—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received September 9—1:03 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>271. Re Legation’s 270, September 8, 3 [<hi rend="italic">2</hi>] p.m. 50,000
                    tons plus pilgrimage supplies and reserve stocks constitutes substantial
                    increase of 1944 supply program though still a compromise as I held irregular
                    and uncontrollable dhow traffic should not be counted in imports at Government
                    disposal. Figure was reached by taking 1944 import consumption as 65,000 tons of
                    which 8,000 were stocks sold and 7,000 were dhow traffic per Saudi figures.</p>
                <p>Method of hold reserve stocks and location not yet agreed but admitted by all
                    that it is physically possible in open-air warehouse at Jidda. Controlled
                    reserves imperative to give confidence and reassurance when famine threatens. I
                    will study problem and report later.</p>
                <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Eddy</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
